The article discusses the recent gun violence in Lewiston, Maine, where a bowling alley and a restaurant became scenes of tragedy. The author expresses condolences and solidarity with the victims and their families, along with support for local authorities in their investigation. They emphasize the need to address the issue of gun violence, stating that it is the leading cause of death for children in the United States. The author calls for the implementation of universal background checks, red flag laws, a ban on high-capacity magazines, and the renewal of the assault weapons ban. They also mention the efforts of the White House Office of Gun Violence Prevention in working towards saving lives.